This scrip download the source from git
The generated package will be installed in /opt so that is can be installed
with another wine in /usr

To integrate with desktop
/usr/share/applications/wine-tkg-git.desktop
Remember that if an installer generate a desktop shortcut
that .desktop file will use the path to the used wine-tkg binary path.
wine puts those classic windows menu application launchers in:
~/.local/share/applications/wine/Programs/

Symbolic links to wine64 and wine
To post install into /usr/bin/ run:

/opt/wine-tkg-staging-fsync-git/symlink_usr_bin.sh
/opt/wine-tkg-staging-fsync-git/symlink_usr_bin.sh --restore
/opt/wine-tkg-staging-fsync-git/symlink_usr_bin.sh --force-no-backup

If /usr/bin/wine is a Symbolic link it will overwrite
else it will backup and hide all wine related binaries
like /usr/bin/.wine.backup

Installing multilib for Slackware 15 is enough to build


backlist wine-tkg to make slackpkg happy
